- - - ( Laravel Configuration ) - - -

- Laravel's configuation files, are stored in the "Config directory",
  each file in "that" directory corresponds to a specific 
  part of the application...
  
  • app.php
  • auth.php
  • cache.php
  • database.php
  • filesystems.php
  • logging.php
  • mail.php
  • queue.php
  • services.php
  • session.php

- all of these "PHP files", "return arrays" of 
  key - value pair "configuration options"
  ( Variables relies on "Environment Variables" )



  ( app.php ):

- contains the basic configuration for the application, e.g..
  • name 
  • app environment
  • if debug mode's enabled // determines if error should be displayed or not ( bool )
  • timezone
  • encryption key
  • etc...